        <mxCell id="gPIo2Yxe_p3ejxSHxQAn-13" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="TODO: I still haven&#39;t figured out exactly the method that embed mapping types into mappings. I wanna avoid having an implicit relation&lt;div&gt;e.g where the mapping includes a mapping type: tt&amp;lt;p,&amp;gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;and i want to relate &amp;lt;p,&amp;gt; to a mapping type instance.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I don&#39;t want to have it included in the string of the name but then included again as a foreign key and have those two be separate, I&#39;d rather have some way that allows those to always be in alignment with each other.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;one idea is to include the mapping type and the location in the name that it needs to be included. problem with that is that it puts limitations and adds extra complexity for multiple mappings in the same instance.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
